President Trump delivered remarks upon his arrival in Japan, where he celebrated the close economic ties between the United States and Japan. He praised the work of Ambassador Hagerty and emphasized the special relationship he has with Prime Minister Abe. President Trump highlighted the ongoing negotiations for a bilateral trade agreement and expressed his desire to address the trade imbalance and ensure fairness and reciprocity. He also mentioned the strong military relationship between the two countries and the large orders of military equipment from Japan. President Trump encouraged increased investments in the United States, citing the country's strong economy and favorable business environment. He mentioned the achievements in deregulation, tax cuts, and job creation, and highlighted the growth in the energy sector. President Trump expressed his hope for the continued deepening and strengthening of economic ties between the United States and Japan during the Reiwa Era.